# MiOS is a bootc-based OCI bootable OS built on top of
# ghcr.io/ublue-os/ucore-hci:stable-nvidia (Universal Blue's HCI variant
# of Fedora CoreOS), with a sibling minimal target on
# quay.io/fedora/fedora-bootc:latest available as Containerfile.minimal.
# The ID_LIKE chain "fedora coreos" preserves CoreOS ancestry for tools
# (zincati, rpm-ostree, bootc) that branch on it; the ID=mios is the new
# canonical identity that fastfetch / motd / postcheck see.
#
# The seven version-bearing fields (VERSION, VERSION_ID, PRETTY_NAME,
# CPE_NAME, BUILD_ID, IMAGE_VERSION, OSTREE_VERSION) are NOT authored here:
# they are PROJECTED at build time from the single SSOT
# mios.toml [meta].mios_version (via /ctx/VERSION -> MIOS_VERSION in
# automation/49-finalize.sh), and drift-check (42) fails the build if the
# committed values above ever diverge from that SSOT. Edit the version in
# mios.toml [meta].mios_version ONLY.
